    {
      "id": "a77d2eab_db05580c",
      "file_path": "snmptrap/check_hb_traps",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 234,
      "message": "if there are spaces in the resulting files, this will have a totally wrong number.\nIf there are newlines in the filename, then it's even worse.\nFor hardening, you cannot assume anything about the filenames.\n\nOne way to find the number of names is\n\nnum_trapd_logs=$( find . -name \"*${trapd_arriving_traps_fname}*\" -exec stat -c FILE {} + | wc -l )\nthis converts each filename to the word FILE and then uses wc to count the lines.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 105,
        "name": "Tony Hansen",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "tony@att.com",
        "username": "TonyLHansen"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-17 20:37:27.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
